"{    \"translations\": [        {            \"english_version\": \"Kenya will not send police officers to Haiti until a new government is formed there. This decision was made after Haiti's prime minister, Ariel Henry, resigned. He had been in Kenya to finalize an agreement to send officers, but gangs took over the capital, Port-au-Prince.\",            \"english_title\": \"Kenya's Decision on Deploying Police to Haiti\",            \"translated_version\": \"Kenya no enviar\u00e1 oficiales de polic\u00eda a Hait\u00ed hasta que haya un nuevo gobierno all\u00ed. Esta decisi\u00f3n se tom\u00f3 despu\u00e9s de que el primer ministro de Hait\u00ed, Ariel Henry, renunciara. \u00c9l hab\u00eda estado en Kenia para finalizar un acuerdo para enviar oficiales, pero pandillas tomaron el control de la capital, Puerto Pr\u00edncipe.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Kenya's Decision on Deploying Police to Haiti\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"In the US, consumer prices rose by 3.2% in February. Core prices, excluding energy and food, increased by 0.4% month on month. This data will be considered by the Federal Reserve in their upcoming meeting.\",            \"english_title\": \"US Consumer Prices and Federal Reserve Meeting\",            \"translated_version\": \"En los EE. UU., los precios al consumidor aumentaron un 3.2% en febrero. Los precios b\u00e1sicos, excluyendo energ\u00eda y alimentos, aumentaron un 0.4% mes a mes. Estos datos ser\u00e1n considerados por la Reserva Federal en su pr\u00f3xima reuni\u00f3n.\",            \"translated_title\": \"US Consumer Prices and Federal Reserve Meeting\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"Britain's foreign secretary called for answers from Israel after reports of abuse of Palestinian medics by Israeli soldiers. The medics claimed they were beaten and mistreated during a raid on a hospital in Gaza.\",            \"english_title\": \"Israeli-Palestinian Conflict and Abuse Allegations\",            \"translated_version\": \"El secretario de Relaciones Exteriores de Gran Breta\u00f1a pidi\u00f3 respuestas a Israel despu\u00e9s de informes de abuso de m\u00e9dicos palestinos por soldados israel\u00edes. Los m\u00e9dicos afirmaron que fueron golpeados y maltratados durante una redada en un hospital en Gaza.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Israeli-Palestinian Conflict and Abuse Allegations\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"The US plans to send a $300m weapons package to Ukraine. However, this amount is deemed insufficient to meet Ukraine's needs. A larger package of $60bn for Ukraine is currently stalled in Congress.\",            \"english_title\": \"US Military Assistance to Ukraine\",            \"translated_version\": \"Los EE. UU. planean enviar un paquete de armas de $300 millones a Ucrania. Sin embargo, esta cantidad se considera insuficiente para satisfacer las necesidades de Ucrania. Un paquete m\u00e1s grande de $60 mil millones para Ucrania est\u00e1 actualmente estancado en el Congreso.\",            \"translated_title\": \"US Military Assistance to Ukraine\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"Romania's president has entered the race to become NATO's secretary-general. Meanwhile, the Bank of Japan governor mentioned some challenges in the Japanese economy, despite signs of recovery.\",            \"english_title\": \"Romania's President in NATO Race and Bank of Japan's Assessment\",            \"translated_version\": \"El presidente de Rumania ha entrado en la carrera para convertirse en secretario general de la OTAN. Mientras tanto, el gobernador del Banco de Jap\u00f3n mencion\u00f3 algunos desaf\u00edos en la econom\u00eda japonesa, a pesar de los signos de recuperaci\u00f3n.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Romania's President in NATO Race and Bank of Japan's Assessment\"        }    ]}"